    "guidance": {
      "whenToUse": "Use to visually represent users or entities with an associated image or initials. Ideal for user profiles, comment sections, team listings, and any context where a compact visual identifier is needed for an individual or organization.",
      "whenNotToUse": "Do not use as a general icon component or for purely decorative elements that do not represent a specific user or entity. Avoid using when complex interactive states or detailed information needs to be displayed directly on the avatar, as it is primarily a display component.",
      "accessibility": "Ensure the underlying 'img' element has a descriptive 'alt' attribute for screen readers. When initials are displayed as a fallback, ensure sufficient color contrast. The component should handle cases gracefully where neither an image nor initials are provided, possibly displaying a generic user icon.",
